cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CV, cs.NE 

This paper is about explaining the predictions of neural network models for natural language processing tasks. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also proposes algorithms for hierarchical explanation, which involves analyzing the interactions between words and phrases, and quantifying their importance. This suggests that the paper could also be relevant to categories such as cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Finally, the paper mentions the use of visualization techniques, which could relate to cs.CV (Computer Vision).
